# hlm3_mix_35m_k16.hlm — operate on the HLM3-Mix 35M K=16 research preview
#
# This script targets the public research-preview checkpoint distributed in
#     hlm3-mix-35m-k16-research-preview-2026-05-14.zip
# (model/model.pt inside the extracted folder).
#
# It walks the canonical energy-language workflow on a realistic, trained
# checkpoint rather than a synthetic toy: observe, modify, verify, restore.
#
# Run:
#     qriton-hlm --script examples/hlm3_mix_35m_k16.hlm

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Load the model and inspect it
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
load hlm3-mix-35m-k16-research-preview-2026-05-14/model/model.pt
info

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Map the energy landscape across all layers
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# `survey-all` reports the basin count and learned beta per layer. The
# expectation on a healthy HLM3 checkpoint is a monotone beta hierarchy:
# shallow layers act as smooth feature mixers, deep layers as sharper
# categorical attractors.
survey-all

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Baseline generation (no surgery yet)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
set tokens 30
generate The history of the city of
generate In a controlled experiment, the researchers

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. Capture a concept from a few short examples at a mid layer
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Mid-stack (L4 in an 8-layer model) is usually the best target: the state
# is no longer raw token mixing and not yet fully categorical, so injected
# concepts compose with downstream layers cleanly.
capture 4 formal The committee convened to deliberate the proposal
capture 4 formal The findings were duly noted and entered into the record
capture 4 formal Per the established protocol the matter was referred onward

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. Inject the captured concept as a new attractor
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# A small strength (0.05 - 0.10) is enough on a 35M model. Larger values
# can collapse neighbouring basins, which the `guard` step below will catch.
set strength 0.08
guard 4 10
inject-concept 4 formal

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 6. Apply the modified W to the live model and inspect the delta
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
apply 4
diff 4
status

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 7. Generate with the modified landscape
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
generate The history of the city of
generate In a controlled experiment, the researchers

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 8. Restore and re-verify (the entire surgery is reversible)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
restore 4
status
generate The history of the city of
